6.2.18  8:41 am   arent making reality videos very simple and easy that it wont affect your progress on bigger projects.

     no

      like youre literally recording your voice and uploading it.

     that's not true, the audio has already been recorded. thousands of hours of audio. what actually takes the most amount of time is crawling through all that and putting together a coherent narrative

      (text isnt necessary if thats the time sink there btw)

      the text/graphics is a very important step, but quite easy because i totally half ass it. and no i'm not going to do it without graphics, but that wouldn't save much time because as i said what takes all the time is essentially re-listening to my entire life and editing it down to a thrilling story. and what you've seen on the reality page represents only a small fraction of what can be done with the material. i have dreams of massive detailed behind the scenes shows, but at some point i have to make a decision as to whether or not i would prefer spend the entire rest of my life making a documentary about the previous part of my life. at some point i will make that turn, but not until i am perhaps less than 10 years from the end of my life
